                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq2">
                                Do automatics cost more to maintain?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Only slightly—and mostly for CVT and DCT types. AMTs are very affordable.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq3">
                                Which sells better in resale—manual or automatic?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                In cities, automatics win. In rural areas, manuals still rule.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq4">
                                Is AMT reliable long term?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Yes! Many owners clock over 75,000 km without issues.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq5">
                                Do automatics offer hill-hold?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Some do—especially new DCTs and CVTs. Older AMTs might not.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="div-line"></div>

                <h3 class="subheading">9. Final Verdict</h3>

                    <a class="for-link" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index"><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub</span></a>
                <div class="pros-cons">
                    <div>
                            <h5 class="subheading">Manuals:</h5>
                        <p>
                            Great for budget buyers, rural roads, or driving enthusiasts.<br>
                            More engaging, slightly more fuel-efficient, and cheaper to maintain.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                            <h5 class="subheading">Automatics:</h5>
                        <p>
                            Perfect for urban driving, families, and beginners.<br>
                            Modern autos are efficient, comfortable, and well-equipped.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                
                    <h5 class="subheading">Still confused? Test drive both.</h5>
                    <p> AMTs can feel jerky if you're used to CVTs. Manuals can be tiring in traffic. Only your own test drive will tell you what <em>feels right</em>.</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">Your Pre-Purchase Checklist</h3>
                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Drive both manual and automatic versions</li>
                        <li>Try AMTs in traffic</li>
                        <li>Check low-speed smoothness (AMT/CVT)</li>
                        <li>Try DCTs under heavy acceleration</li>
                        <li>See how hill-starts feel (especially in AMTs)</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <div class="div-line"></div>

                    <h3 class="subheading">Final Word</h3>
                <p>There's no one-size-fits-all answer. But in 2025, both manuals and automatics have matured. Whether you're watching your wallet or prioritizing convenience, India has an option that fits your style.</p>
                <p>Take a test drive, compare, and choose the car that'll <span class="font-weight-700">make every drive feel right</span>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
